channel.title: Papers with Code: Latest (unofficial)
channel.description: As a disclaimer, this is an unofficial feed and has no affiliation with Papers with Code.

item.title: Design of Negative Sampling Strategies for Distantly Supervised Skill Extraction
item.description: We introduce a manually annotated evaluation benchmark for skill extraction based on the ESCO taxonomy, on which we validate our models.

item.title: CovidMis20: COVID-19 Misinformation Detection System on Twitter Tweets using Deep Learning Models
item.description: Online news and information sources are convenient and accessible ways to learn about current issues.

item.title: Adversarial Inter-Group Link Injection Degrades the Fairness of Graph Neural Networks
item.description: We hope our findings raise awareness about this issue in our community and lay a foundation for the future development of GNN models that are more robust to such attacks.

item.title: Time-of-Day Neural Style Transfer for Architectural Photographs
item.description: Architectural photography is a genre of photography that focuses on capturing a building or structure in the foreground with dramatic lighting in the background.

item.title: Generalized Intent Discovery: Learning from Open World Dialogue System
item.description: Traditional intent classification models are based on a pre-defined intent set and only recognize limited in-domain (IND) intent classes.

item.title: SpaDE: Improving Sparse Representations using a Dual Document Encoder for First-stage Retrieval
item.description: Sparse document representations have been widely used to retrieve relevant documents via exact lexical matching.

item.title: A Meta-level Analysis of Online Anomaly Detectors
item.description: The behavior of the detectors is correlated with the characteristics of different datasets (i. e., meta-features), thereby providing a meta-level analysis of their performance.

item.title: A deep variational free energy approach to dense hydrogen
item.description: We present a deep generative model-based variational free energy approach to the equations of state of dense hydrogen.

item.title: Rethink about the Word-level Quality Estimation for Machine Translation from Human Judgement
item.description: While the post-editing effort can be used to measure the translation quality to some extent, we find it usually conflicts with the human judgement on whether the word is well or poorly translated.

item.title: Predicting Brain Multigraph Population From a Single Graph Template for Boosting One-Shot Classification
item.description: A central challenge in training one-shot learning models is the limited representativeness of the available shots of the data space.

item.title: Investigating the Predictive Reproducibility of Federated Graph Neural Networks using Medical Datasets
item.description: To the best of our knowledge, this presents the first work investigating the reproducibility of federated GNN models with application to classifying medical imaging and brain connectivity datasets.

item.title: A Tale of HodgeRank and Spectral Method: Target Attack Against Rank Aggregation Is the Fixed Point of Adversarial Game
item.description: From the perspective of the dynamical system, the attack behavior with a target ranking list is a fixed point belonging to the composition of the adversary and the victim.

item.title: PSAQ-ViT V2: Towards Accurate and General Data-Free Quantization for Vision Transformers
item.description: In this paper, we propose PSAQ-ViT V2, a more accurate and general data-free quantization framework for ViTs, built on top of PSAQ-ViT.

item.title: Expressive Reasoning Graph Store: A Unified Framework for Managing RDF and Property Graph Databases
item.description: Resource Description Framework (RDF) and Property Graph (PG) are the two most commonly used data models for representing, storing, and querying graph data.

item.title: Investigating Bias with a Synthetic Data Generator: Empirical Evidence and Philosophical Interpretation
item.description: Machine learning applications are becoming increasingly pervasive in our society.

item.title: Don't Judge a Language Model by Its Last Layer: Contrastive Learning with Layer-Wise Attention Pooling
item.description: Recent pre-trained language models (PLMs) achieved great success on many natural language processing tasks through learning linguistic features and contextualized sentence representation.

item.title: Class-Level Logit Perturbation
item.description: However, limited studies have explicitly explored for the perturbation of logit vectors.

item.title: Adaptive Discretization using Voronoi Trees for Continuous-Action POMDPs
item.description: A Voronoi tree is a Binary Space Partitioning (BSP) that implicitly maintains the partition of a cell as the Voronoi diagram of two points sampled from the cell.

item.title: Self-supervised motion descriptor for cardiac phase detection in 4D CMR based on discrete vector field estimations
item.description: Simultaneously, deep learning-based deformable image registration is able to estimate discrete vector fields which warp one time step of a CMR sequence to the following in a self-supervised manner.

item.title: Defense against Privacy Leakage in Federated Learning
item.description: Federated Learning (FL) provides a promising distributed learning paradigm, since it seeks to protect users privacy by not sharing their private training data.

item.title: Learning to Solve Multiple-TSP with Time Window and Rejections via Deep Reinforcement Learning
item.description: We propose a manager-worker framework based on deep reinforcement learning to tackle a hard yet nontrivial variant of Travelling Salesman Problem (TSP), \ie~multiple-vehicle TSP with time window and rejections (mTSPTWR), where customers who cannot be served before the deadline are subject to rejections.

item.title: Entity Tagging: Extracting Entities in Text Without Mention Supervision
item.description: Detection and disambiguation of all entities in text is a crucial task for a wide range of applications.

item.title: SVNet: Where SO(3) Equivariance Meets Binarization on Point Cloud Representation
item.description: Precisely, the presence of scalar features makes the major part of the network binarizable, while vector features serve to retain rich structural information and ensure SO(3) equivariance.

item.title: PointScatter: Point Set Representation for Tubular Structure Extraction
item.description: Inspired by this, we propose PointScatter, an alternative to the segmentation models for the tubular structure extraction task.

item.title: StoryDALL-E: Adapting Pretrained Text-to-Image Transformers for Story Continuation
item.description: Hence, we first propose the task of story continuation, where the generated visual story is conditioned on a source image, allowing for better generalization to narratives with new characters.

item.title: Resource Allocation to Agents with Restrictions: Maximizing Likelihood with Minimum Compromise
item.description: Our focus is on resource allocation problems where agents may have restrictions that make them incompatible with some resources.

item.title: CSL: A Large-scale Chinese Scientific Literature Dataset
item.description: The CSL can serve as a Chinese corpus.

item.title: Leveraging Large Language Models for Robot 3D Scene Understanding
item.description: Specifically, we introduce three paradigms for leveraging language for classifying rooms in indoor environments based on their contained objects: (i) a zero-shot approach, (ii) a feed-forward classifier approach, and (iii) a contrastive classifier approach.

item.title: SmartKex: Machine Learning Assisted SSH Keys Extraction From The Heap Dump
item.description: A commonly used method in digital forensics is to extract data from the main memory of a digital device.

item.title: "Some other poor soul's problems": a peer recommendation intervention for health-related social support
item.description: Our results support the usefulness and demand for peer recommendation and suggest benefits to evaluating larger peer recommendation interventions.

item.title: Switchable Online Knowledge Distillation
item.description: Instead of focusing on the accuracy gap at test phase by the existing arts, the core idea of SwitOKD is to adaptively calibrate the gap at training phase, namely distillation gap, via a switching strategy between two modes -- expert mode (pause the teacher while keep the student learning) and learning mode (restart the teacher).

item.title: Semantic-Preserving Adversarial Code Comprehension
item.description: Based on the tremendous success of pre-trained language models (PrLMs) for source code comprehension tasks, current literature studies either ways to further improve the performance (generalization) of PrLMs, or their robustness against adversarial attacks.

item.title: Open-Domain Dialog Evaluation using Follow-Ups Likelihood
item.description: Automatic evaluation of open-domain dialogs remains an unsolved problem.

item.title: Wasserstein Distributional Learning
item.description: To overcome this fundamental issue, we propose Wasserstein Distributional Learning (WDL), a flexible density-on-scalar regression modeling framework that starts with the Wasserstein distance $W_2$ as a proper metric for the space of density outcomes.

item.title: CustOmics: A versatile deep-learning based strategy for multi-omics integration
item.description: Recent advances in high-throughput sequencing technologies have enabled the extraction of multiple features that depict patient samples at diverse and complementary molecular levels.

item.title: CenterFormer: Center-based Transformer for 3D Object Detection
item.description: It then uses the feature of the center candidate as the query embedding in the transformer.

item.title: Lexical Simplification Benchmarks for English, Portuguese, and Spanish
item.description: To showcase the usability of the dataset, we adapt two state-of-the-art lexical simplification systems with differing architectures (neural vs.\ non-neural) to all three languages (English, Spanish, and Brazilian Portuguese) and evaluate their performances on our new dataset.

item.title: Partial Observability during DRL for Robot Control
item.description: Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) has made tremendous advances in both simulated and real-world robot control tasks in recent years.

item.title: Communication-Efficient and Privacy-Preserving Feature-based Federated Transfer Learning
item.description: In order to improve the communication efficiency, we in this paper propose the feature-based federated transfer learning as an innovative approach to reduce the uplink payload by more than five orders of magnitude compared to that of existing approaches.

item.title: Deep Feature Statistics Mapping for Generalized Screen Content Image Quality Assessment
item.description: The underlying mechanism of the proposed approach is based upon the wild assumption that the SCIs, which are not physically acquired, still obey certain statistics that could be understood in a learning fashion.

item.title: Prototypical few-shot segmentation for cross-institution male pelvic structures with spatial registration
item.description: The prowess that makes few-shot learning desirable in medical image analysis is the efficient use of the support image data, which are labelled to classify or segment new classes, a task that otherwise requires substantially more training images and expert annotations.

item.title: Attitude-Guided Loop Closure for Cameras with Negative Plane
item.description: To tackle this issue, we propose a loop closure framework with a new outlier rejection method based on the unit length representation, to improve the accuracy of LF-VIO.

item.title: Predicting the Next Action by Modeling the Abstract Goal
item.description: It is through the submission of this paper that our method is currently the new state-of-the-art for action anticipation in EK55 and EGTEA Gaze+ https://competitions. codalab. org/competitions/20071#results Code available at https://github. com/debadityaroy/Abstract_Goal

item.title: GenLoco: Generalized Locomotion Controllers for Quadrupedal Robots
item.description: In this work, we introduce a framework for training generalized locomotion (GenLoco) controllers for quadrupedal robots.

item.title: Model interpretation using improved local regression with variable importance
item.description: A fundamental question on the use of ML models concerns the explanation of their predictions for increasing transparency in decision-making.

item.title: FiBiNet++:Improving FiBiNet by Greatly Reducing Model Size for CTR Prediction
item.description: Click-Through Rate(CTR) estimation has become one of the most fundamental tasks in many real-world applications and various deep models have been proposed to resolve this problem.

item.title: Bending the Future: Autoregressive Modeling of Temporal Knowledge Graphs in Curvature-Variable Hyperbolic Spaces
item.description: The chronological hierarchies between knowledge graphs at different timestamps are represented by embedding the knowledge graphs as vectors in a common hyperbolic space.

item.title: Fairness in Forecasting of Observations of Linear Dynamical Systems
item.description: In machine learning, training data often capture the behaviour of multiple subgroups of some underlying human population.

item.title: SANCL: Multimodal Review Helpfulness Prediction with Selective Attention and Natural Contrastive Learning
item.description: With the boom of e-commerce, Multimodal Review Helpfulness Prediction (MRHP), which aims to sort product reviews according to the predicted helpfulness scores has become a research hotspot.

item.title: Detecting Network-based Internet Censorship via Latent Feature Representation Learning
item.description: To estimate the probability of censorship events from the inferred latent features, we rely on a densely connected multi-layer neural network model.
